GERMANY
Dong Kingman, the award winning Chinese-American artist, travels the world sketching and painting
the beautiful, the monumental and the picturesque. His watercolors grace more than forty
permanent museum and private collections in the USA and abroad.
Mr. Kingman's watercolor of a castle overlooking the Rhine River is typical of the varied and
beautiful landscape of Germany. The people are industrious and their major cities are bustling with
trade and commerce. But they also know how to enjoy life. Germans are among the most culture-
conscious people in the world. Sixty-three cities have permanent opera companies and even small
towns have their own repertory theatres and orchestras. Inter-Continental Hotels are located in
Cologne, Dusseldorf, Frankfurt, Hanover, and Hamburg. Pan Am serves many cities in Germany
including Frankfurt, Hamburg, Munich, Stuttgart, Berlin, and Nuremburg.
